Method Detail

deserialize

public void deserialize()
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        WSDLException,
                        SOAPException
Reads the SOAP payload and converts the parameters that is encapsulated in the payload to Java parameters. This is the entry point to the deserialization process. At this point the parser is pointing to the Envelope element.

The converted parameters are stored in the Envelope passed in the constructor.

Specified by:
deserialize in interface SOAPDeserializer
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if an error occurs during deserialization.

deserialize

public java.lang.Object deserialize(Type type,
                                    org.kxml.parser.XmlParser parser,
                                    java.lang.String defaultTypeName)
                             throws java.io.IOException,
                                    SOAPException
Takes a Type and converts it to a Java representation. The Type is either a XSDType, SimpleType.
Specified by:
deserialize in interface SOAPDeserializer
Parameters:
type - Type that contains the definition of the data type encapsulated in the parser. It is either a XSDType or SimpleType.
XmlParser - that is pointing to the StartTag of the element that contains the Type value.
defaultTypeName - the name of the type. This is typically necessary for anonymous simple type and complex types. For named types, this may be left null. For anonymous types, the deserializer uses the name to look up the type mapping registry to determine the appropriate deserializer class.
Returns:
Object the type encapsulated as Java object.
Throws:
SOAPException - if the type is not supported.
java.io.IOException - if an error occurs while processing the payload.

skipTillBody

protected void skipTillBody()
                     throws java.io.IOException
Reads the XmlParser until the element is encountered. The parser is positioned so that the next parser.peek() or parser.read() returns the element after the element.
